    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework demonstrates HIGH assurance for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated pedicle screw construct. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 1 vs. required level 3) is considered acceptable given that F1717 is a standardized protocol and the single test condition is directly specified by the standard. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support regulatory submission.",
